1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,253
[OLSEN] <i>We will do what Emil Padua wants.</i>

2
00:00:03,336 --> 00:00:05,005
<i>We'll bring back his money.</i>

3
00:00:05,088 --> 00:00:07,048
<i>Not for him, but for our families.</i>

4
00:00:07,132 --> 00:00:09,884
[LIAM] <i>We will find a way to save them.</i>

5
00:00:09,968 --> 00:00:13,221
<i>Maybe you could give them</i>
<i>a little more time?</i>

6
00:00:13,304 --> 00:00:16,224
<i>What you're asking from them</i>
<i>is very difficult.</i>

7
00:00:16,307 --> 00:00:18,977
<i>How much money is it anyway?</i>
<i>300 million?</i>

8
00:00:19,060 --> 00:00:20,603
<i>I can raise that.</i>

9
00:00:20,687 --> 00:00:22,105
<i>Just give me time.</i>

10
00:00:22,188 --> 00:00:24,274
<i>Stop playing games with me, Senator.</i>

11
00:00:24,357 --> 00:00:26,151
<i>Your son was at La Playa Roja</i>

12
00:00:26,234 --> 00:00:31,489
<i>and he got dragged into</i>
<i>what Magnus Roja did to me.</i>

13
00:00:31,573 --> 00:00:33,867
<i>He ruined my daughter's life!</i>

14
00:00:33,950 --> 00:00:36,661
<i>He made her his mistress</i>
<i>and then abandoned her!</i>

15
00:00:36,745 --> 00:00:39,748
<i>Because of you Rojas, we lost our land.</i>

16
00:00:39,831 --> 00:00:42,083
<i>Because you stuck your nose in,</i>

17
00:00:42,167 --> 00:00:43,918
<i>my brother and I went to jail.</i>

18
00:00:44,002 --> 00:00:45,295
<i>Who's your brother?</i>

19
00:00:45,378 --> 00:00:47,464
<i>Homer Sebastian.</i>

20
00:00:51,092 --> 00:00:53,094
- [AREZA] What's his condition?
- [OFFICER] Critical, sir.

21
00:00:53,178 --> 00:00:54,721
<i>He actually survived.</i>

22
00:00:54,804 --> 00:00:56,347
<i>Bad weeds really do never die.</i>

23
00:00:56,431 --> 00:00:58,600
<i>Get me all available information</i>
<i>on Captain Jacinto.</i>

24
00:00:58,683 --> 00:01:02,395
<i>I want to know what connection</i>
<i>he has with Emil Padua,</i>

25
00:01:02,479 --> 00:01:04,022
<i>and who his other accomplices are.</i>

26
00:01:04,564 --> 00:01:07,233
<i>I think I might know where…</i>

27
00:01:07,317 --> 00:01:09,778
<i>where they hid what you're looking for.</i>

28
00:01:09,861 --> 00:01:11,196
<i>How come you know?</i>

29
00:01:11,279 --> 00:01:13,740
<i>He was talking to one of your men.</i>

30
00:01:13,823 --> 00:01:15,492
<i>He mentioned a place.</i>

31
00:01:15,575 --> 00:01:18,703
<i>What you're looking for</i>
<i>might be hidden there.</i>

32
00:01:20,872 --> 00:01:22,040
<i>- I didn't find--</i>
<i>- Liam!</i>

33
00:01:22,999 --> 00:01:24,209
<i>I dropped Papa!</i>

34
00:01:24,292 --> 00:01:25,627
<i>Are those your father's ashes?</i>

35
00:01:25,710 --> 00:01:27,420
<i>Are you sure these are ashes?</i>

36
00:01:27,504 --> 00:01:28,588
[OLSEN] <i>Sand?</i>

37
00:01:33,676 --> 00:01:35,428
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

38
00:01:35,512 --> 00:01:40,809
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYS, FADES]

39
00:01:42,227 --> 00:01:43,561
[LIAM] I'm sorry, bro,

40
00:01:43,645 --> 00:01:45,688
but we have to go.

41
00:01:46,606 --> 00:01:48,733
Let's check the secret cove.

42
00:01:48,817 --> 00:01:51,778
They might've hidden it far from the
resort so the police wouldn't find it.

43
00:01:51,861 --> 00:01:56,241
[STAMMERING] Bro,
why was Papa's urn filled with sand?

44
00:01:56,324 --> 00:01:58,368
I've been talking to him all my life.

45
00:01:58,451 --> 00:01:59,494
- I thought it was him.
- Bro…

46
00:01:59,577 --> 00:02:01,746
- Where are his ashes?
- Olsen!

47
00:02:01,830 --> 00:02:03,623
Let's think about that later.

48
00:02:03,706 --> 00:02:05,291
It'll be far worse

49
00:02:05,375 --> 00:02:10,713
if we, our families, and the hostages
are the ones turning into ashes

50
00:02:10,797 --> 00:02:13,550
because we're not back by twelve
with their money.

51
00:02:15,176 --> 00:02:16,136
[SNIFFLES]

52
00:02:16,219 --> 00:02:18,471
- Let's get moving.
- [OLSEN] Let's go.

53
00:02:18,555 --> 00:02:21,015
- [CELL PHONE RINGING]
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

54
00:02:21,099 --> 00:02:23,393
- [SNIFFLES]
- [RINGING STOPS]

55
00:02:23,476 --> 00:02:25,520
- [SNIFFLES]
- [MUSIC FADES OUT]

56
00:02:25,603 --> 00:02:27,355
- Son?
- Ma?

57
00:02:28,273 --> 00:02:29,941
Listen carefully.

58
00:02:30,024 --> 00:02:34,195
I might know where you can find
the money and the jewelry.

59
00:02:34,863 --> 00:02:36,322
You know where the money is?

60
00:02:36,406 --> 00:02:40,034
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

61
00:02:40,118 --> 00:02:43,705
Go to the cottage by the old docks.

62
00:02:43,788 --> 00:02:44,831
There's a loft there.

63
00:02:44,914 --> 00:02:46,374
Wait a sec, I know that boathouse.

64
00:02:46,457 --> 00:02:50,712
[LIAM] <i>The one with the fish drawing</i>
<i>on the ceiling, hidden.</i>

65
00:02:50,795 --> 00:02:51,880
Is the money there?

66
00:02:54,716 --> 00:02:58,136
[STAMMERING] Maybe. It might be there.

67
00:02:58,219 --> 00:02:59,596
How did you know?

68
00:03:01,055 --> 00:03:04,058
You don't have much time.
Just listen to me.

69
00:03:04,142 --> 00:03:05,393
Look for it!

70
00:03:05,476 --> 00:03:12,025
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

71
00:03:19,282 --> 00:03:20,450
[TENSE MUSIC STING]

72
00:03:31,336 --> 00:03:38,259
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

73
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:17,423
[THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING]

74
00:04:18,967 --> 00:04:20,885
[COUGHS, EXHALES]

75
00:04:20,969 --> 00:04:23,096
We haven't been here in a long time.

76
00:04:24,389 --> 00:04:31,312
[MUSIC BECOMES SUSPENSEFUL]

77
00:04:32,230 --> 00:04:33,648
[MUSIC FADES]

78
00:04:38,569 --> 00:04:40,571
<i>- What's that for?</i>
- [SENTIMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]

79
00:04:40,655 --> 00:04:42,573
<i>This one? For that?</i>

80
00:04:43,157 --> 00:04:45,368
<i>Our secret hiding place.</i>

81
00:04:45,451 --> 00:04:48,496
<i>Well, now it's no longer a secret.</i>

82
00:04:48,579 --> 00:04:53,084
[SENTIMENTAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

83
00:04:56,629 --> 00:04:58,715
<i>Do you want to play while I'm drawing?</i>

84
00:04:58,798 --> 00:05:00,091
<i>Papa gave this to me.</i>

85
00:05:00,717 --> 00:05:02,260
<i>You're lucky.</i>

86
00:05:03,219 --> 00:05:04,512
<i>Your dad's nice.</i>

87
00:05:04,595 --> 00:05:09,600
<i>Not everyone has a dad</i>
<i>who gives gifts like that.</i>

88
00:05:10,226 --> 00:05:12,854
<i>I don't have one anymore.</i>

89
00:05:15,857 --> 00:05:19,152
<i>Why? Where's your dad?</i>

90
00:05:19,235 --> 00:05:20,528
<i>He's dead.</i>

91
00:05:21,321 --> 00:05:23,531
<i>I didn't even meet him.</i>

92
00:05:25,158 --> 00:05:27,201
<i>Do you want to share with me?</i>

93
00:05:27,952 --> 00:05:29,871
<i>Share?</i>

94
00:05:29,954 --> 00:05:31,831
<i>Your dad?</i>

95
00:05:31,914 --> 00:05:33,374
<i>No, silly!</i>

96
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:35,209
<i>We'll share this PSP.</i>

97
00:05:35,293 --> 00:05:36,836
<i>Really?</i>

98
00:05:36,919 --> 00:05:38,171
[GRUNTS ENCOURAGINGLY]

99
00:05:40,506 --> 00:05:42,091
<i>Thank you!</i>

100
00:05:42,175 --> 00:05:45,845
[GAME NOISES ON PSP]

101
00:05:45,928 --> 00:05:47,180
<i>Cool!</i>

102
00:05:47,263 --> 00:05:49,932
[GUNFIRE IN GAME]

103
00:05:50,016 --> 00:05:51,726
[TENSE MUSIC STING]

104
00:05:51,809 --> 00:05:53,561
[SENTIMENTAL MUSIC FADES]

105
00:05:53,644 --> 00:05:59,942
[THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING]

106
00:06:00,026 --> 00:06:01,319
- [OLSEN] Be careful.
- [CHAIR SQUEAKS]

107
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:03,404
[LIAM GRUNTS]

108
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:07,867
[OLSEN] Hand that to me.

109
00:06:07,950 --> 00:06:08,868
There.

110
00:06:08,951 --> 00:06:10,870
[OLSEN] Got it.

111
00:06:10,953 --> 00:06:13,164
[MUSIC BECOMES TENSE]

112
00:06:13,247 --> 00:06:14,415
[WOOD PLANK THUDS]

113
00:06:15,541 --> 00:06:16,501
[MUSIC FADES]

114
00:06:17,085 --> 00:06:17,919
Olsen.

115
00:06:18,002 --> 00:06:20,880
[TENSE MUSIC RESUMES]

116
00:06:20,963 --> 00:06:23,049
- [LIAM GRUNTS]
- Just this one?

117
00:06:27,428 --> 00:06:29,680
- There's more?
- There's more.

118
00:06:29,764 --> 00:06:31,265
Wait.

119
00:06:31,349 --> 00:06:33,059
Let's check what's inside.

120
00:06:33,142 --> 00:06:34,185
[BAG UNZIPS]

121
00:06:35,978 --> 00:06:39,816
- [LINE RINGING]
- [PANTING]

122
00:06:39,899 --> 00:06:41,484
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

123
00:06:41,567 --> 00:06:43,361
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

124
00:06:43,444 --> 00:06:44,946
[RINGING CONTINUES]

125
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:49,325
<i>We've found it!</i>

126
00:06:51,285 --> 00:06:53,704
They've found our millions.

127
00:06:55,665 --> 00:06:57,083
[EMIL CHUCKLING]

128
00:06:58,209 --> 00:07:00,545
But don't celebrate yet.

129
00:07:00,628 --> 00:07:02,463
Your mission's not over.

130
00:07:02,547 --> 00:07:05,758
<i>If you miss the deadline,</i>

131
00:07:05,842 --> 00:07:10,179
<i>if our millions go missing,</i>
<i>or if anything's not there,</i>

132
00:07:12,348 --> 00:07:14,225
<i>you know what will happen.</i>

133
00:07:16,227 --> 00:07:17,854
[LIAM] Let's go!

134
00:07:19,230 --> 00:07:25,153
[SINISTER MUSIC PLAYING]

135
00:07:25,236 --> 00:07:27,280
[EMIL LAUGHING MENACINGLY]

136
00:07:27,363 --> 00:07:28,614
[MAN] Whoo!

137
00:07:30,116 --> 00:07:31,868
[LAUGHING MENACINGLY]

138
00:07:32,910 --> 00:07:35,371
[SINISTER MUSIC CONTINUES]

139
00:07:39,417 --> 00:07:40,501
What's that?

140
00:07:40,585 --> 00:07:42,420
- [OLSEN GROANS]
- [TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]

141
00:07:42,503 --> 00:07:43,463
Relax.

142
00:07:43,546 --> 00:07:45,465
[CLICKS]

143
00:07:45,548 --> 00:07:46,841
Souvenir.

144
00:07:48,217 --> 00:07:49,469
I found it here.

145
00:07:52,054 --> 00:07:53,306
Bro.

146
00:07:53,890 --> 00:07:57,894
Those guns in the gun vault
in the security office…

147
00:07:58,519 --> 00:07:59,770
Think they're still there?

148
00:07:59,854 --> 00:08:03,858
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

149
00:08:03,941 --> 00:08:05,109
Right. You're right.

150
00:08:09,822 --> 00:08:10,740
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

151
00:08:14,577 --> 00:08:19,916
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

152
00:08:19,999 --> 00:08:21,959
[MACKY] It's a good thing
they found the money.

153
00:08:23,419 --> 00:08:24,921
Or else we'd be dead.

154
00:08:25,004 --> 00:08:26,464
Why?

155
00:08:26,547 --> 00:08:28,508
Do we know what they're planning next?

156
00:08:28,591 --> 00:08:33,262
Even if we give them that money,
in the end, they will still kill us.

157
00:08:33,346 --> 00:08:37,517
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

158
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:40,019
I won't abandon you.

159
00:08:40,102 --> 00:08:41,103
[MACKY] Dad.

160
00:08:41,187 --> 00:08:43,898
Is what Emil said true?

161
00:08:45,858 --> 00:08:47,902
That you're a corrupt politician.

162
00:08:51,030 --> 00:08:53,908
- We will get out of this.
- Dad! Why, Dad?

163
00:08:53,991 --> 00:08:56,244
That's not what I'm asking.

164
00:08:56,327 --> 00:09:00,790
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

165
00:09:01,958 --> 00:09:03,501
[HEAVY SIGH]

166
00:09:10,132 --> 00:09:12,093
After this ordeal,

167
00:09:13,511 --> 00:09:15,930
I'll fix everything I've done wrong.

168
00:09:16,013 --> 00:09:22,478
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

169
00:09:39,662 --> 00:09:42,123
[PAPER RUSTLES]

170
00:09:42,206 --> 00:09:45,626
[THUDS, CLATTERS]

171
00:09:47,295 --> 00:09:49,297
How's the tunnel, Engineer?

172
00:09:50,464 --> 00:09:54,135
The surface is muddy,
but the bottom is solid.

173
00:09:54,218 --> 00:09:56,262
Feels like concrete.

174
00:09:56,345 --> 00:09:59,515
There's also sandstone,
so it's hard to dig.

175
00:10:00,224 --> 00:10:04,895
Uh, because of that,
we haven't dug very far yet.

176
00:10:04,979 --> 00:10:07,565
We've only reached about one meter.

177
00:10:08,232 --> 00:10:11,736
How many more meters
until we hit the sewer line?

178
00:10:11,819 --> 00:10:14,530
- [MIKE] About six more meters.
- [DIGGING CONTINUES]

179
00:10:14,614 --> 00:10:19,160
The hospital foundation is close
to the sewage corridor anyway.

180
00:10:19,243 --> 00:10:21,037
After that, it's the river.

181
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:26,417
So once we hit the last layer
of the concrete slab,

182
00:10:27,710 --> 00:10:30,046
we'll be connected
to the underground system.

183
00:10:33,466 --> 00:10:35,801
That leads straight
to the maintenance passage.

184
00:10:36,761 --> 00:10:38,471
If the ground is hard…

185
00:10:38,554 --> 00:10:43,643
- [PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [THUDS, DIGGING]

186
00:10:43,726 --> 00:10:45,686
…then blow it up.

187
00:10:48,064 --> 00:10:50,358
You know that I get impatient easily.

188
00:10:50,441 --> 00:10:53,527
We can't waste time here.

189
00:10:53,611 --> 00:10:56,697
My delivery boys are on their way.

190
00:10:59,950 --> 00:11:02,370
How many hours before it collapses?

191
00:11:02,453 --> 00:11:05,539
Uh, if there is no heavy movement,

192
00:11:05,623 --> 00:11:08,709
it should stay stable for a few hours.

193
00:11:08,793 --> 00:11:10,878
Enough for an escape run.

194
00:11:10,961 --> 00:11:13,798
As long as we move fast.

195
00:11:13,881 --> 00:11:15,966
[CHUCKLES WRYLY]

196
00:11:16,050 --> 00:11:17,551
Look at that.

197
00:11:18,260 --> 00:11:20,137
You're actually useful.

198
00:11:21,514 --> 00:11:23,349
Especially you, Architect.

199
00:11:24,183 --> 00:11:27,436
You're close to dying,
but you're still useful.

200
00:11:28,354 --> 00:11:29,897
Don't worry,

201
00:11:29,980 --> 00:11:33,901
this will be your final project,
Architect Minnie Del Rosario.

202
00:11:34,485 --> 00:11:35,486
Okay?

203
00:11:36,404 --> 00:11:38,697
Just make sure

204
00:11:38,781 --> 00:11:41,033
this is done right.

205
00:11:41,117 --> 00:11:44,412
Because we're going through
there together.

206
00:11:45,121 --> 00:11:48,249
If that collapses, you go down with it.

207
00:11:50,209 --> 00:11:51,794
Including your daughter.

208
00:11:51,877 --> 00:11:57,675
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

209
00:12:00,344 --> 00:12:02,596
Make sure you fix that.

210
00:12:02,680 --> 00:12:04,014
Do it properly.

211
00:12:05,599 --> 00:12:12,606
[UNSETTLING MUSIC SWELLS]

212
00:12:18,904 --> 00:12:20,322
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

213
00:12:20,406 --> 00:12:26,704
- [STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]
- [LIAM, OLSEN PANTING]

214
00:12:32,501 --> 00:12:33,878
[GUN VAULT DOOR CLATTERS]

215
00:12:35,963 --> 00:12:41,552
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

216
00:12:41,635 --> 00:12:43,012
[LIAM EXHALES SHARPLY]

217
00:12:43,095 --> 00:12:44,430
Ah, shit.

218
00:12:49,643 --> 00:12:51,479
[BAG ZIP OPENS]

219
00:12:51,562 --> 00:12:52,730
[THUDS]

220
00:12:58,569 --> 00:13:04,992
- [STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [GUNS CLATTERING]

221
00:13:08,204 --> 00:13:09,413
Let's go.

222
00:13:09,497 --> 00:13:10,539
Come on.

223
00:13:10,623 --> 00:13:14,251
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

224
00:13:22,968 --> 00:13:26,514
You shouldn't have attempted
to get her out.

225
00:13:27,348 --> 00:13:29,058
You put her in even more danger.

226
00:13:29,141 --> 00:13:31,185
Because we thought
she had already been treated.

227
00:13:31,268 --> 00:13:35,481
And we knew that once she was treated,
she would go straight to jail.

228
00:13:35,564 --> 00:13:38,567
It will take a few days to fully recover
from the infection.

229
00:13:38,651 --> 00:13:40,653
This is a gunshot wound.

230
00:13:41,237 --> 00:13:43,781
She is vulnerable to internal bleeding

231
00:13:43,864 --> 00:13:45,616
and delayed infection.

232
00:13:45,699 --> 00:13:48,035
She needs close monitoring

233
00:13:49,036 --> 00:13:52,831
and antibiotics for at least one week.

234
00:13:52,915 --> 00:13:53,749
[GWEN] One week?!

235
00:13:55,334 --> 00:13:57,586
We won't be staying here long, Doc.

236
00:13:57,670 --> 00:14:01,090
Just do what you need to do.

237
00:14:01,882 --> 00:14:03,968
I've already given her a sedative.

238
00:14:07,471 --> 00:14:10,558
I still have another patient to attend to.
I also need to check--

239
00:14:10,641 --> 00:14:13,143
Why should I care about your patient?

240
00:14:14,228 --> 00:14:15,521
Just stay here.

241
00:14:18,315 --> 00:14:19,650
[DOOR CLOSES]

242
00:14:29,618 --> 00:14:31,203
How is my daughter?

243
00:14:31,287 --> 00:14:32,872
The doctor is monitoring her.

244
00:14:33,956 --> 00:14:35,249
Right, Doc?

245
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:39,378
Do your job well, Doc.

246
00:14:39,461 --> 00:14:42,089
Unless you want to end up in the ICU.

247
00:14:42,172 --> 00:14:47,761
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

248
00:14:51,140 --> 00:14:56,729
[MUSIC TURNS GLUM]

249
00:15:04,403 --> 00:15:07,448
Boss, what's the update on our exit plan?

250
00:15:09,158 --> 00:15:13,829
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

251
00:15:13,913 --> 00:15:14,955
[MIKE] Come on.

252
00:15:15,831 --> 00:15:16,957
Hurry.

253
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:21,378
[MIKE] Come here. We need to take cover.

254
00:15:21,462 --> 00:15:22,546
Boss, it's ready.

255
00:15:22,630 --> 00:15:23,589
- [MINNIE GRUNTS]
- [MAN] It's ready?

256
00:15:23,672 --> 00:15:24,965
Yes, it's ready.

257
00:15:25,049 --> 00:15:26,175
- Daddy…
- It's okay.

258
00:15:26,258 --> 00:15:27,343
- Ready!
- [MINNIE SCREAMS]

259
00:15:27,426 --> 00:15:28,302
[CLICKS]

260
00:15:28,385 --> 00:15:31,847
- [LOUD EXPLOSION]
- [MINNIE WHIMPERS, SCREAMS]

261
00:15:31,931 --> 00:15:33,140
[DEBRIS CRASHES]

262
00:15:33,223 --> 00:15:35,643
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

263
00:15:35,726 --> 00:15:37,186
Did you hear that?

264
00:15:38,812 --> 00:15:40,981
[SMOKE HISSES]

265
00:15:44,985 --> 00:15:46,820
- [MEN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]
- [COUGHING]

266
00:15:46,904 --> 00:15:50,407
- [MADDIE WHIMPERS]
- [COUGHING]

267
00:15:51,867 --> 00:15:56,956
- [MADDIE, MINNIE WHIMPERING]
- [ALL COUGHING]

268
00:15:57,665 --> 00:16:00,167
- [WHIMPERS]
- It's okay.

269
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:02,294
- [MADDIE CRIES, COUGHS]
- [MINNIE BREATHES HEAVILY]

270
00:16:03,879 --> 00:16:05,673
The construction is moving fast.

271
00:16:07,466 --> 00:16:11,637
In no time, our millions
will be in our hands.

272
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:13,681
The delivery boys are on their way back.

273
00:16:13,764 --> 00:16:16,934
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

274
00:16:18,018 --> 00:16:24,316
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

275
00:16:25,859 --> 00:16:28,070
<i>Hello? Hello, Jericho?</i>

276
00:16:28,153 --> 00:16:29,196
[JACINTO]<i> Greta?</i>

277
00:16:29,279 --> 00:16:30,781
<i>What's going on?</i>

278
00:16:30,864 --> 00:16:32,825
<i>We had a deal, remember?</i>

279
00:16:32,908 --> 00:16:34,368
[LIAM] <i>Ma?</i>

280
00:16:34,451 --> 00:16:35,828
<i>Who are you talking to?</i>

281
00:16:37,788 --> 00:16:38,831
<i>Who's Jericho?</i>

282
00:16:39,873 --> 00:16:42,960
[STAMMERS]<i> He's…</i>
<i>he's my contact at the police station.</i>

283
00:16:43,043 --> 00:16:44,003
<i>Uh…</i>

284
00:16:44,086 --> 00:16:46,046
<i>Nothing's still happened here.</i>

285
00:16:46,130 --> 00:16:48,090
<i>We can't get out.</i>

286
00:16:48,173 --> 00:16:50,050
<i>Is any help still coming here?</i>

287
00:16:52,261 --> 00:16:54,054
<i>Get away from my mom, or I'll shoot!</i>

288
00:16:54,138 --> 00:16:55,556
<i>No, don't!</i>

289
00:16:55,639 --> 00:16:57,558
<i>He's here to help us.</i>

290
00:16:57,641 --> 00:17:01,061
<i>He's that Jericho guy</i>
<i>you talked to on the phone, right?</i>

291
00:17:01,145 --> 00:17:03,564
<i>Yes, he's the police officer I contacted.</i>

292
00:17:03,647 --> 00:17:06,066
<i>I came to this island to save you.</i>

293
00:17:06,150 --> 00:17:08,861
<i>I saw you talking to those bastards!</i>

294
00:17:08,944 --> 00:17:10,696
<i>I'm not the enemy, Liam.</i>

295
00:17:10,779 --> 00:17:12,614
<i>One of them almost killed you!</i>

296
00:17:12,698 --> 00:17:15,451
<i>Liam, he's our ally!</i>
<i>You have to believe me!</i>

297
00:17:18,245 --> 00:17:23,417
<i>…there wouldn't have been</i>
<i>a hostage taking at La Playa Roja.</i>

298
00:17:25,085 --> 00:17:26,211
<i>Yes.</i>

299
00:17:27,588 --> 00:17:29,673
<i>He is the mastermind.</i>

300
00:17:31,675 --> 00:17:34,219
<i>The real boss of all of us.</i>

301
00:17:34,303 --> 00:17:35,304
<i>It's not me.</i>

302
00:17:40,184 --> 00:17:41,518
<i>Let's go.</i>

303
00:17:41,602 --> 00:17:44,938
<i>- Come on! Grab him.</i>
<i>- Wait! Wait!</i>

304
00:17:46,940 --> 00:17:49,485
[LIAM] <i>Does Mama have something</i>
<i>to do with all of this?</i>

305
00:17:50,778 --> 00:17:57,326
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

306
00:18:05,375 --> 00:18:09,421
[LINE RINGING]

307
00:18:09,505 --> 00:18:10,964
We're close to the port.

308
00:18:16,470 --> 00:18:20,474
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

309
00:18:20,557 --> 00:18:22,142
[OLSEN GRUNTS]

310
00:18:28,190 --> 00:18:31,985
Take good care of my daughter, Doctor.

311
00:18:33,237 --> 00:18:35,322
I need to go upstairs now.

312
00:18:35,405 --> 00:18:37,741
Boss Emil, I'll come with you.

313
00:18:37,825 --> 00:18:40,702
Magnus Roja and I still have
unfinished business.

314
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:58,262
[MAGNUS] Did you hear that?

315
00:18:58,345 --> 00:19:00,639
I wonder how is Olsen doing.

316
00:19:02,182 --> 00:19:04,309
Well, they already got
the money and the jewelry,

317
00:19:04,393 --> 00:19:06,186
so no one will touch them for now.

318
00:19:06,270 --> 00:19:09,815
I think we're safe for now.

319
00:19:13,652 --> 00:19:16,238
Do you know Homer personally?

320
00:19:16,321 --> 00:19:21,702
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

321
00:19:21,785 --> 00:19:22,953
I'm sorry.

322
00:19:23,036 --> 00:19:24,204
Wendy, it looks like…

323
00:19:25,831 --> 00:19:28,125
It seems like I'm the one
to blame for now.

324
00:19:29,626 --> 00:19:33,922
Almost all of them seem to have
a personal grudge against me.

325
00:19:34,006 --> 00:19:36,508
I was just asking a question.

326
00:19:36,592 --> 00:19:38,260
I'm not blaming anyone.

327
00:19:39,386 --> 00:19:40,971
I know his boss.

328
00:19:42,598 --> 00:19:45,017
He was a regular VIP at La Playa Roja.

329
00:19:46,518 --> 00:19:48,604
I didn't know that

330
00:19:49,605 --> 00:19:51,440
gun smuggling was his business.

331
00:19:53,192 --> 00:19:57,321
He used to go to the resort often
when you were still there.

332
00:19:57,404 --> 00:20:00,032
Mr. Dela Peña. Do you know him?

333
00:20:00,115 --> 00:20:02,326
I was housekeeping back then.

334
00:20:02,409 --> 00:20:05,829
We didn't really interact much
with the guests.

335
00:20:12,211 --> 00:20:13,462
Uh…

336
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:16,506
His bodyguard…

337
00:20:18,967 --> 00:20:20,719
it turns out, is Lucas' brother.

338
00:20:20,802 --> 00:20:27,434
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

339
00:20:32,481 --> 00:20:34,942
[MAN] <i>What really happened?</i>
<i>Why did you leave the resort?</i>

340
00:20:35,025 --> 00:20:36,735
<i>I don't want to talk about it.</i>

341
00:20:37,569 --> 00:20:39,029
<i>I will take care of you.</i>

342
00:20:41,114 --> 00:20:42,366
Wendy.

343
00:20:43,492 --> 00:20:46,453
Again, I'm very sorry.

344
00:20:47,746 --> 00:20:49,706
Uh, I tried to--

345
00:20:49,790 --> 00:20:52,334
Well, I demanded that they release you.

346
00:20:52,417 --> 00:20:54,503
That you not be dragged into this anymore.

347
00:20:56,088 --> 00:20:58,006
But they didn't listen to me.

348
00:21:04,554 --> 00:21:05,806
Yes, sir.

349
00:21:09,268 --> 00:21:10,519
Boss.

350
00:21:12,479 --> 00:21:19,319
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

351
00:21:31,623 --> 00:21:35,544
<i>We'll think of a way to get inside</i>
<i>and defuse the bombs.</i>

352
00:21:35,627 --> 00:21:38,046
<i>I've waited a long time for this day.</i>

353
00:21:38,130 --> 00:21:38,964
<i>Wendy?</i>

354
00:21:39,047 --> 00:21:41,967
[LUCAS] <i>Is she the woman you said</i>
<i>you used to live with?</i>

355
00:21:42,050 --> 00:21:44,344
<i>Are you still thinking</i>
<i>about your father's ashes?</i>

356
00:21:44,428 --> 00:21:45,929
<i>Where could his real ashes be?</i>

357
00:21:46,013 --> 00:21:47,431
[DADO] <i>Help us carry this.</i>

358
00:21:47,514 --> 00:21:49,016
<i>Don't think for a second</i>

359
00:21:49,099 --> 00:21:51,351
<i>that I've forgotten about</i>
<i>what you did to my brother.</i>

360
00:21:51,435 --> 00:21:53,729
<i>Your brother died because of you.</i>

361
00:21:53,812 --> 00:21:56,023
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [GRUNTS, GROANS]

362
00:21:56,106 --> 00:21:57,899
- [DADO]<i> I dare you to say that again!</i>
- [GRUNTS]

363
00:21:57,983 --> 00:21:59,067
<i>No!</i>
